We updated our RIO firmware to the 2025 v2 from patch1.
Before that the old (non-Vivid) radio worked fine with the WPI code.
After the update the old radio works just fine with RIO1, but not with RIO2.

I get

Warning ﻿﻿ 44002 ﻿﻿ Ping Results: ﻿link-bad﻿, DS radio(.4)-bad﻿, robot radio(.1)-GOOD﻿, roboRIO(.2)-bad﻿, FMS-bad﻿﻿ Driver Station

in the driver station when connected. I restarted robot, RIO, radio separately and in combinations with no success.

Anyone has old radio working with RIO2 after updating the NI firmware to 2025v2?
We tried reflashing the radio with the 2024 Radio Configuration Utility, and also connected the radio to RIO2 with and without POE. Same result.
